FBIS3-37069 "drsov030_f_94007" FBIS-SOV-94-030 Document Type:Daily Report 14 Feb 1994 National Affairs Defense Minister Appoints New Deputy LD1102233994 Kiev UNIAN in Ukrainian 2030 GMT 11 Feb 94 LD1102233994 Kiev UNIAN Language: Ukrainian Article Type:BFN [Text] Kiev--A UNIAN correspondent learned from sources close to Ukraine's Defense Ministry that Army General Vitaliy Radetskyy, Ukraine's defense minister, issued an order approving a new deputies staff. As before, Staff Colonel General Anatoliy Lopata is first deputy defense minister. Colonel General Ivan Bizhan, the deputy defense minister also remains in office. Colonel General Hryhoriy Mykhalchenko, the deputy defense minister for rear services, and Ivan Oliynyk, the deputy defense minister for armaments, are joined by the head of the Main Directorate for Land Forces who was promoted to their position. His previous post remains vacant.
